za.sabob.olive.ps
Class SqlParam

java.lang.Object
  za.sabob.olive.ps.SqlParam
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class SqlParam
extends Object
implements Serializable

Provides a class for setting a single named parameter.

This class is used by SqlParams to define the named parameters to populate a PreparedStatement with.

Example usage: 

 SqlParams params = new SqlParams();
 SqlParam param = new SqlParam("age", 21);
 params.set(param);
 param = new SqlParam("name", "Steve);
 params.set(param);

 // Inernally SqlParams creates SqlParam instances
 params.setInt("code", 123");
SqlParam also contains all the data found on PreparedStatement.setXXX methods.

The data represented by SqlParams are:

  • name - the SQL parameter name
  • value - the SQL parameter value
  • sqlType - the type of the parameter
  • scale - the number of digits after the decimal point. Used for decimal parameter
  • typeName - the fully-qualified name of an SQL user-defined type; ignored if the parameter is not a user-defined type or Types.REF
